 she serves as catalyst for women’s consumer fun. This change inspires stories of ordinary girls—and even one boy—striving to embody the maiko ideal, engaging in masquerades that highlight questions of personal choice, gender performance, and national identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aGeishaszJapanzKyotoxHistoryy21st century. 0aPopular culturezJapanxHistoryy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520968943zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968943423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520968943/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSLb2021